verbose_text: In Stinckens ' paper animals, at an age of 26 weeks, showed a significantly lower GDF8 expression in homozygous than heterozygous animals [XREF_BIBR]; in contrast, in Guimaraes ' work, a commercial synthetic line of pigs showed a reduced backfat thickness, a higher lean meat content and less marbling in heterozygous animals when compared with in homozygous wild-type and homozygous mutant animals [XREF_BIBR].
